nit: strlen + strncpy is equivalent to strcpy, it doesn't provide anything because you are still finding the length.

Do you actually need to rewrite the interface name each time? Some calls overwrite the flags, but AFAIK nothing should touch the ifname

I've had strcpy before but got error from gerrit that I used should use strlcpy and I agree. Just following recommendation. 

I've seen it sometimes where struct get wiped, it's not guaranteed, so I erred on the safe side.

Then don't use `strlen()`, just use the length of the string.

Heck, don't use strncpy, just use `std::copy_n(iface_name.c_str(), iface_name_.size()+1, ifr.ifr_name)` since you don't need any of the checks.
adjusted thank you.
